## C1 Decision Engine: Figma Image Checklist

All images should be abstract/conceptual — no real product data. Export PNG at 2x. Save to `/static/projects/images/` using `c1-decision-engine-[descriptor].png`.

- [ ] **Hero image** (`c1-decision-engine-hero.png`) — Abstract UI shell suggesting a complex enterprise policy tool. Dark or neutral toned, with placeholder rule rows and a component-style layout.
- [ ] **Problem: before state** (`c1-decision-engine-before.png`) — Diagram showing fragmentation: multiple disconnected spreadsheet grids or document icons with arrows going everywhere. Intentionally chaotic.
- [ ] **System hierarchy diagram** (`c1-decision-engine-system-hierarchy.png`) — Three-tier layered diagram: Tokens → Core Components → Reusable Patterns. Clean and simple.
- [ ] **Rule Cell anatomy** (`c1-decision-engine-rule-cell.png`) — Annotated component diagram of a single rule cell. Labels like "Upstream dependency," "Validation state," "Logic input." Most important image in the study.
- [ ] **Before/after modular workflow** (`c1-decision-engine-before-after.png`) — Two-column split: left shows spreadsheet chaos, right shows clean modular card workflow.

